</psychological_feature>
</act>
</rule>
</event>
s that represent some object. Many <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../775/775.xml">
algorithm</link>s in machine learning require a numerical representation of objects, since such representations facilitate processing and
statistical analysis. When representing images, the feature values might correspond to the pixels of an image, when representing texts perhaps to term occurrence frequencies. <p>

The <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../370/32370.xml">
vector space</link> associated with these vectors is often called the <it><link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../063/5245063.xml">
feature space</link></it>. In order to reduce the dimensionality of the feature space, a number of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../867/579867.xml">
dimensionality reduction</link> techniques can be employed.</p>


